metatags.dc.description: Poker is a card game played with a normal deck of 52 cards. Sometimes, additional cards called "jokers" are also used. In straight or draw poker, each player is normally dealt a hand of five cards. Depending on the variant, players then discard and redraw cards, trying to improve their hands. Bets are placed at each discard step. The number of possible distinct five-card hands is equal to the number of possible ways of picking five cards out of a deck of 52, namely  N=(52;...
